    "remarks": {
      "sha256": "1a7cab388a9add44ba6df1adc1993aaf09aefdb2ac585259ffa527a7e268cafb",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "Brun's sieve implies $h(x) \\to \\infty$ as $x\\to \\infty$."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "f0a4a3a161136485ca9c53e29ea463ccbebce34ab1937dd84704837eb2e1f4e9",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $d_n=p_{n+1}-p_n$, where $p_n$ is the $n$th prime. Let $h(x)$ be maximal such that for some $n<x$ the numbers $d_n,d_{n+1},\\ldots,d_{n+h(x)-1}$ are all distinct. Estimate $h(x)$. In particular, is it true that\\[h(x) >(\\log x)^c\\]for some constant $c>0$, and\\[h(x)=o(\\log x)?\\]"
    }
  },
